<p>
<seg id=1> On World AIDS Day, U.S. President Clinton pledged to provide new financial aid to prevent such fatal diseases, including more research funding. </seg>
<seg id=2> Clinton plans to increase AIDS research funding at the National Institutes of Health by 30 percent. </seg>
<seg id=3> He is also preparing to announce that he will provide US$10 million in funds to care for AIDS orphans. </seg>
<seg id=4> The Clinton Administration has indicated that following this increase in research funding, this will be the largest single investment of U.S. public funds in AIDS research. </seg>
</p>
